programme.desc: Dirk has been a busy restaurant owner for as long as he can remember. Long hours running three different establishments kept him from ever having time to take care of himself. Now, he's retired and ready to get on with life, but can't seem to get a date.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Back to Hog Heaven
programme.desc: Once comfortable on the back of her husband's Harley, this biker babe has lost all confidence in her looks. Now her aging appearance is keeping her from the fun things in life – all that used to make her happy.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Shopping For a New Look
programme.desc: Karyn is a busy working wife and mother of three, whose current frumpy appearance isn't matching the way she feels inside. It's the goal of our experts to fashion Karyn a more youthful, trendsetting look as we try make her look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 35 year old Richard Power was living life to the limits – and it showed. A year later, we recap Richard's rocky relationship with our femme fatale of flair – and see whether a catch-up with Nicky will set things straight.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Bringing Out The Spunk
programme.desc: Cat has a dream job working with rock stars and she lost 125 pounds with diet and exercise. She's worked hard to get where she is, but its left her looking more 30-something than 20-something. Our team is ready to jam on her makeover and do what it takes.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Trevanions are delighted when Fatani asks Danny to take an aggressive hippo off his hands. As they prepare for its arrival Sarah gets a bit of a shock when her mother Caroline beats the hippo to the post.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Business is looking up at Leopard's Den but Sarah is feeling agitated. Caroline thinks it because Simon, her ex husband and Evan and Olivia's Dad, is arriving from England to get married. But Sarah has other things on her mind.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny is undertaking a drugs trial at Leopard's Den. But de-worming wildebeest isn't Caroline's idea of fun. She hates animals and finds the whole business mind-numbingly boring.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Du Plessis is in a foul mood. It's his 60th birthday and he has no intentions of celebrating it. But the Trevanions have other ideas and Caroline is organising a surprise party.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 9
programme.desc: Rugby fan Dave and Musician Howard are about to discover what life is like when Mum goes on strike. Whilst mum is being pampered in a five star luxury hotel.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 10
programme.desc: Military man Mark and fireman Richard are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their worn-out wives Sharon and Tara have gone on strike and are spending three days at a luxury spa.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: It is the most extraordinary case diplomat Tom Walter has ever seen - 18 and 16 year-old Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson have been abandoned by their parents and left to fend for themselves.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's judgement day for abandoned Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson. After hours of questioning, Indonesian Immigration officials have confiscated the boy's passports and put them under strict house arrest.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: 59-year-old Joanne came to Thailand for a body makeover. She's had a tummy tuck and liposuction to look her best for her daughter's wedding. She loses her passport and the wound from her tummy tuck gets infected, Joanne finds herself stuck in Thailand.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Wayne has no money, no passport and a mountain of debt. Homeless and out of options, he's back at the Consulate in Bali with sobering news. But can consular officer, Tom Walter trust his story?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: 56-year-old Michael is living every parent's worst nightmare. His six-year-old son Dylan has been missing for three months now. His ex-wife didn't return him after a routine weekend visit and now he fears that she's trying to smuggle him out of Bali.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 1
programme.desc: Muriwai lifeguard's first rescue of the season is of an unexpected nature and on a remote part of the beach. Lifeguards rush to the aid of a distraught 18-year-old girl whose been sucked into a treacherous hole.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 2
programme.desc: Lifeguards struggle to keep swimmers safe as swift rips sweep them out of the flagged area. But for one boogie boarder it's too late. The young guns are put to the test as a surfer is pounded by huge swells and dragged across jagged rocks.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 3
programme.desc: It's looking like another perfect day for the mounting crowd at Muriwai Beach, but lifeguards soon have a crisis on their hands as a full scale search is mounted for a young boy.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 4
programme.desc: A surfer washes up on Muriwai Beach and lifeguards are unsure what's wrong with him. Lifeguards could be forced to shut the beach because of an invasion of a swarm of jellyfish.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 5
programme.desc: With the summer season in full swing the veteran guards decide to teach the Rookie's some new tricks. A shark sighting has the entire beach on full alert. And the relentless rips prove too much for one Canadian tourist.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 6
programme.desc: Inviting surf conditions cause chaos's as the mix of boards and swimmers ends in tears. Could engine failure be disastrous for Muriwai lifeguards as a group of inexperience surfers are swept out to sea. And the pounding surf shows the IRB crew whose boss.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 7
programme.desc: Record crowds leave lifeguards frustrated as veteran Garth McCullough's worst fear comes true. Training turns real as young rookie Mackenzie makes her first rescue.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 8
programme.desc: Muriwai reputations are put on the line as they battle for supremacy at the State National Championship. It's back to work for Doctor Slim as the sand dunes bite back. And the young guns step up to keep Danger Beach safe.

programme.title: Motorheads: Hans Herrmann
programme.desc: Portrait of Hans Herrmann, who was famous Formula 1- and sports car driver in 1950 to 1970. He also won the 24 Hours of Le Mans.

programme.title: Motorheads: Sabine Schmitz
programme.desc: Portrait of Sabine Schmitz, a very successful race driver from Germany and the so-called "Queen of the Nordschleife".

programme.title: Motorheads: Prince Leopold von Bayern
programme.desc: Portrait of Prince Leopold von Bayern, who is a famous race driver from Germany. The Bavarian prince competed in races till 1998 and is now a brand ambassador for BMW.

programme.title: Motorheads: Henry Ford
programme.desc: Portrait of Henry Ford, a man who wanted to improve the world and became a pioneer in the automobile industry by introducing the Model T.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: The Yas Marina Story
programme.desc: The Yas Marina Circuit in Abu Dhabi is the most glamorous race track of the Formula One. Khaled Qubaysi takes us for a spin on this exclusive behind-the-scenes look at the famous F1 race track.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: X-Raid Rally Dakar
programme.desc: Stéphane Peterhansel is the most successful driver in the history of the Dakar Rally. Along with the German team X-Raid he wins the 2012 and 2013 editions of this prestigious marathon in a Mini Countryman.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Ice Action Finland
programme.desc: Former World Rally Champion Armin Schwarz is a legend behind the wheels. Now he is instructing other talented people in driving a 300 hp Subaru WRX STI rally car on the snowy and icy, but also breathtaking landscape of Finland.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Racechip Challenge
programme.desc: More power and yet better fuel economy? With chip tuning this is supposed to be possible. We want to check this out and send two teams on a road trip with a difference. From Uhingen near Stuttgart in Germany, we travel to Barcelona and back.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: New Car Purchase Experience
programme.desc: A new car. A new driving experience. A new lifestyle. But which paths do four wheels, an engine and a whole lot of sheet metal take until the first drive? This is a question probably only asked by a few.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: 90 Years BMW Motor Bike
programme.desc: Precision, high-tech, high quality: After nine decades of eventful history ""BMW Motor Bikes"" are seen today are being almost too perfect. A story between tradition and innovation with ups and downs.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: The Car of the Future
programme.desc: The car of the future - this is how it might look: Aerodynamic, light and quiet. And with almost no fuel consumption. This is how we could soon travel on roads. But is a car like this just a pipe dream of engineers?

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Isle of Mann TT 2015 Documentary
programme.desc: The Tourist Trophy on the British Isle of Man is the most famous motorcycle race in the world. TT Sidecar champion Klaus Klaffenböck and racing expert Lenz Leberkern explore the fascination behind the TT Isle of Man.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Rains Down

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Red Highway

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Fate Worst Than Death

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: The Master Key
